==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spalt
<hw>Spalt</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. G.
<ets>spalt</ets>stein, from <ets>spalten</ets> to split. See 1st
<er>Spell</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Metal.)</fld> <def>Spelter.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spalt</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Spalt
<hw>Spalt</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See 1st <er>Spell</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Liable to break or split; brittle; <as>as,
<ex>spalt</ex> timber</as>.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Heedless; clumsy; pert; saucy.</def> <mark>[Prov.
Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spalt</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Spalt
<hw>Spalt</hw>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos> <ety>[Cf. OE. <ets>spalden</ets>.
See <er>Spalt</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <def>To split off; to cleave
off, as chips from a piece of timber, with an ax.</def> <mark>[Prov.
Eng. & Local, U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spalting knife</ent>⟦br⟧
